responses.s0_q0: Yes: The organization has a comprehensive, current privacy policy addressing personal information management.
responses.s0_q1: Yes: All these elements are clearly addressed in the policy.
responses.s0_q2: No: The policy is not available free of charge or in an appropriate form.
responses.s0_q3: Partially: The organization tries but may not always accommodate requests.
responses.s1_q0: Yes: Individuals can interact anonymously or with a pseudonym in most cases.
responses.s1_q1: Yes: Exceptions are only made when legally required or impracticable.
responses.s2_q0: Partially: Most information is necessary, but some may not be.
responses.s2_q1: Yes: Sensitive information is collected only with consent or as legally permitted.
responses.s2_q2: Yes: Collection methods are always lawful and fair.
responses.s2_q3: Yes: Information is collected directly unless an exception applies.
responses.s3_q1: Partially: Information is occasionally retained unnecessarily.
responses.s4_q0: Partially: Notification is incomplete or inconsistent.
responses.s5_q0: Partially: Use/disclosure for secondary purposes occurs without proper basis.
responses.s5_q1: Partially: Secondary use/disclosure is sometimes unrelated or unexpected.
responses.s5_q2: Partially: Guidelines are only partially followed.
responses.s5_q3: Yes: Information is de-identified as required before disclosure.
responses.s6_q0: Partially: Direct marketing occurs without proper consent or authority.
